      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's... exactly it. It feels so much more honest to just admit it's over. Everyone else is just performing, acting like things are gonna be fine, but it's all a lie. If the planet is just gonna burn anyway, then all these plans, all these expectations we have for ourselves... they're just heavy, right? It's like carrying around weight for a trip that's already canceled. Does it even make sense to stay in the struggle once you realize there's no actual exit strategy for humanity?",
